WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:14.097 --> 00:00:18.059
{\an8}All right. everybody.
settle down!

3
00:00:18.060 --> 00:00:19.310
{\an8}Good.

4
00:00:19.311 --> 00:00:21.437
{\an8}Now. Robby has something
important to say.

5
00:00:21.438 --> 00:00:22.897
I know that this isn't easy.

6
00:00:22.898 --> 00:00:25.024
We're going to help you
address any challenges

7
00:00:25.025 --> 00:00:26.400
that you might be having.

8
00:00:26.401 --> 00:00:28.236
If you have any concerns.
just raise your hand.

9
00:00:28.237 --> 00:00:31.030
- Emma. write all this down.
- Dr. Mohan.

10
00:00:31.031 --> 00:00:33.282
Medication orders aren't
coming up from the pharmacy.

11
00:00:33.283 --> 00:00:35.243
Check with the clinical
pharmacist

12
00:00:35.244 --> 00:00:36.953
to see if it's in the PDS.

13
00:00:36.954 --> 00:00:38.538
If it's not.
then give the third copy

14
00:00:38.539 --> 00:00:40.331
of the order sheet to Dr. Nordt.

15
00:00:40.332 --> 00:00:42.083
We're gonna need more people
to run it down.

16
00:00:42.084 --> 00:00:43.417
We'll work on it. Langdon.

17
00:00:43.418 --> 00:00:45.002
I can't find
the patient clipboards.

18
00:00:45.003 --> 00:00:47.255
Clipboards need to stay here
for orders and labs.

19
00:00:47.256 --> 00:00:49.048
Wait. so how do
we write our notes?

20
00:00:49.049 --> 00:00:51.634
Take the T sheet to the
bedside. not the whole chart.

21
00:00:51.635 --> 00:00:53.469
Same goes for nursing notes.

22
00:00:53.470 --> 00:00:55.263
- Princess.
- Fax machine is down.

23
00:00:55.264 --> 00:00:57.640
- Error message E6.
- What the hell does that mean?

24
00:00:57.641 --> 00:00:59.934
- You can check the manual.
- There isn't one.

25
00:00:59.935 --> 00:01:01.227
Okay. Perlah.

26
00:01:01.228 --> 00:01:02.812
why don't you take your phone
out to the base?

27
00:01:02.813 --> 00:01:04.939
{\an8}See if you can get service.
find a manual online.

28
00:01:07.734 --> 00:01:08.943
{\an8}What else?

29
00:01:08.944 --> 00:01:10.528
Ogilvie. put your hand down.
Santos.

30
00:01:10.529 --> 00:01:12.196
We've gotten
a few CT results back

31
00:01:12.197 --> 00:01:13.531
but nothing on plain films.

32
00:01:13.532 --> 00:01:15.283
That's probably
because they're all sitting

33
00:01:15.284 --> 00:01:17.451
on the portable machine
not getting to radiology.

34
00:01:17.452 --> 00:01:19.120
- I'll take care of this.
- You be patient.

35
00:01:19.121 --> 00:01:22.123
Help each other. Thank you.

36
00:01:22.124 --> 00:01:24.125
We need to call in extra help.

37
00:01:24.126 --> 00:01:26.460
- At 3:00 p.m. on a holiday?
- I know people. buddy.

38
00:01:26.461 --> 00:01:29.630
I have a 32-year-old woman
with severe abdominal pain.

39
00:01:29.631 --> 00:01:31.299
- Do we have a bed?
- Not at the moment.

40
00:01:31.300 --> 00:01:32.633
- I'll take her.
- Incoming.

41
00:01:32.634 --> 00:01:33.634
Thank you.

42
00:01:33.635 --> 00:01:35.469
Santos. Javadi. you're up.

43
00:01:35.470 --> 00:01:37.972
Trauma one's open.

44
00:01:37.973 --> 00:01:39.432
12-year-old Jude Augustin...

45
00:01:39.433 --> 00:01:41.684
firecracker exploded.
nondominant left hand.

46
00:01:41.685 --> 00:01:43.644
Good vitals. 25 of fent so far.

47
00:01:43.645 --> 00:01:44.979
Any other injuries?

48
00:01:44.980 --> 00:01:46.814
No. but seems to have
lost two of his fingers.

49
00:01:46.815 --> 00:01:48.357
- Did you bring 'em?
- Blown to bits.

50
00:01:48.358 --> 00:01:50.192
- It really hurts.
- I'm sure it does.

51
00:01:50.193 --> 00:01:52.028
We'll do something for that.

52
00:01:52.029 --> 00:01:54.031
- Parents?
- Not on scene.

53
00:01:56.241 --> 00:01:57.283
Ready?

54
00:01:57.284 --> 00:01:59.327
One. two. three.

55
00:01:59.328 --> 00:02:00.786
Hey. Jude.

56
00:02:00.787 --> 00:02:02.997
do you know your mom
or your dad's telephone number?

57
00:02:02.998 --> 00:02:05.374
No. But I know my sister's.

58
00:02:05.375 --> 00:02:07.126
Okay.

59
00:02:07.127 --> 00:02:09.545
- Good breath sounds.
- Abdomen nontender.

60
00:02:09.546 --> 00:02:10.963
Heart rate 112.

61
00:02:10.964 --> 00:02:12.673
Put this around
his left forearm.

62
00:02:12.674 --> 00:02:14.383
- Is that good?
- That is very good.

63
00:02:14.384 --> 00:02:16.844
I want to do another 25 of fent
before we open this bandage.

64
00:02:16.845 --> 00:02:18.596
Can you tell us what happened?

65
00:02:18.597 --> 00:02:21.515
- My friends had firecrackers.
- 25 fent on board.

66
00:02:21.516 --> 00:02:24.185
I lit one. and it went off fast.

67
00:02:24.186 --> 00:02:26.187
I-I dropped it. but...

68
00:02:26.188 --> 00:02:28.064
We're gonna take
your bandage off now. okay?

69
00:02:28.065 --> 00:02:30.024
- I don't want to see.
- You don't have to.

70
00:02:30.025 --> 00:02:31.817
Just look at me.

71
00:02:31.818 --> 00:02:33.194
Okay.

72
00:02:33.195 --> 00:02:36.030
Cutting.

73
00:02:36.031 --> 00:02:38.074
Sorry.

74
00:02:38.075 --> 00:02:39.825
You're doing great.

75
00:02:42.537 --> 00:02:45.247
That looks like a lot more
than a firecracker.

76
00:02:45.248 --> 00:02:47.750
More like an M-80
or a cherry bomb.

77
00:02:47.751 --> 00:02:49.710
It's really good
that you dropped it.

78
00:02:49.711 --> 00:02:51.545
You saved the rest of your hand.

79
00:02:51.546 --> 00:02:53.089
Digits 4 and 5 avulsed.

80
00:02:53.090 --> 00:02:55.591
Distal metacarpals 4 and 5
also gone with exposed bone.

81
00:02:55.592 --> 00:02:57.259
Soft-tissue damage
on the palmar aspect.

82
00:02:57.260 --> 00:02:59.845
less so on dorsal...
some burns on wound edges.

83
00:02:59.846 --> 00:03:04.058
Jude. can you bend your
fingers for me up and down?

84
00:03:04.059 --> 00:03:06.018
- Really good job.
- Really good job.

85
00:03:06.019 --> 00:03:08.396
- How bad is it?
- You lost two fingers.

86
00:03:08.397 --> 00:03:11.107
But it seems like the rest
are gonna be okay.

87
00:03:11.108 --> 00:03:13.401
Oh. no. I fucked up!

88
00:03:13.402 --> 00:03:15.903
All right. can we do
a wrist block for the pain?

89
00:03:15.904 --> 00:03:18.781
I want to do a very detailed
motor and sensory exam first.

90
00:03:18.782 --> 00:03:21.450
We're gonna continue
our exam now. okay. Jude?

91
00:03:24.746 --> 00:03:26.080
Okay. thanks.

92
00:03:26.081 --> 00:03:28.416
ICU can take her
after the next neuro exam.

93
00:03:28.417 --> 00:03:29.792
The ICU?

94
00:03:29.793 --> 00:03:32.044
It's just so she
can be monitored for the rest

95
00:03:32.045 --> 00:03:33.921
of the day.

96
00:03:33.922 --> 00:03:36.966
4 millimeters and reactive.

97
00:03:36.967 --> 00:03:38.217
Mel.

98
00:03:38.218 --> 00:03:40.928
- 4 millimeters and reactive.
- Yep. got it.

99
00:03:40.929 --> 00:03:43.598
I could sort of make out
your hand.

100
00:03:46.810 --> 00:03:48.936
Can you cover your good eye?

101
00:03:48.937 --> 00:03:52.440
How many fingers
am I holding up?

102
00:03:52.441 --> 00:03:53.567
Three.

103
00:03:55.444 --> 00:03:56.861
That's good news.

104
00:03:56.862 --> 00:04:00.030
- So the medicine worked?
- She's out of the woods?

105
00:04:00.031 --> 00:04:01.407
Um. possibly.

106
00:04:01.408 --> 00:04:02.575
It's...

107
00:04:02.576 --> 00:04:05.745
Okay. um. cover your eye again.

108
00:04:05.746 --> 00:04:08.664
{\an8}All right. what do you see?

109
00:04:08.665 --> 00:04:12.544
{\an8}- Top line is E.
- All right. and the next one?

110
00:04:14.838 --> 00:04:16.839
{\an8}Nothing.

111
00:04:16.840 --> 00:04:20.134
Okay. well. that's 20/200.

112
00:04:20.135 --> 00:04:21.343
Meaning?

113
00:04:21.344 --> 00:04:23.471
Uh. what a healthy eye
can see at 200 feet.

114
00:04:23.472 --> 00:04:24.805
she can see at 20 feet.

115
00:04:24.806 --> 00:04:27.683
- Is that good?
- Yeah. It's much better.

116
00:04:27.684 --> 00:04:30.811
Um. and it can continue
to improve over time.

117
00:04:30.812 --> 00:04:33.522
Thank you. Dr. King.

118
00:04:33.523 --> 00:04:36.150
Um. I'm gonna take a quick break

119
00:04:36.151 --> 00:04:37.943
- before my deposition.
- Mm-hmm.

120
00:04:37.944 --> 00:04:40.154
So I'll let Robby know
that I'm off the clock

121
00:04:40.155 --> 00:04:42.323
- for the time being.
- Good luck.

122
00:04:42.324 --> 00:04:43.658
Thanks.

123
00:04:45.869 --> 00:04:47.620
- Mel.
- Hey.

124
00:04:47.621 --> 00:04:48.996
You have a visitor in chairs.

125
00:04:48.997 --> 00:04:52.249
- What? Who?
- Said she's your sister.

126
00:04:52.250 --> 00:04:53.627
Becca?

127
00:04:57.672 --> 00:04:59.507
Yep. You have heat exhaustion.

128
00:04:59.508 --> 00:05:01.550
It usually gets better
with Aleve.

129
00:05:01.551 --> 00:05:03.344
but today was really bad.

130
00:05:03.345 --> 00:05:05.638
- Same pain you had before?
- Mm-hmm.

131
00:05:05.639 --> 00:05:07.681
- From a cyst?
- I think so.

132
00:05:07.682 --> 00:05:10.017
I have PCOS.

133
00:05:10.018 --> 00:05:12.686
Is the. uh... is the pain
always on your left?

134
00:05:12.687 --> 00:05:13.979
Today it is.

135
00:05:13.980 --> 00:05:16.857
We will check a UA
and urine pregnancy test.

136
00:05:16.858 --> 00:05:18.400
and I'll give you
a shot of Toradol.

137
00:05:18.401 --> 00:05:21.070
It's something a little
stronger for the pain.

138
00:05:21.071 --> 00:05:22.780
I'm not pregnant. I promise.

139
00:05:22.781 --> 00:05:26.033
- No. we have to.
- It's hospital policy.

140
00:05:26.034 --> 00:05:29.703
You guys still write stuff
down on paper?

141
00:05:29.704 --> 00:05:32.373
Today we do. yeah.

142
00:05:39.256 --> 00:05:40.548
Are you a doctor?

143
00:05:40.549 --> 00:05:42.842
I've been waiting hours
to be seen.

144
00:05:42.843 --> 00:05:44.176
- Quick question...
- Oh.

145
00:05:44.177 --> 00:05:47.388
- Hey. watch the walker.
- This thing is useless.

146
00:05:47.389 --> 00:05:49.890
- Sorry. I just. um. um...
- we're really busy.

147
00:05:49.891 --> 00:05:51.934
And someone
will see you in a second.

148
00:05:54.312 --> 00:05:57.273
- Becca.
- Mel. hi.

149
00:05:57.274 --> 00:06:00.150
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah. I have a stomachache.

150
00:06:00.151 --> 00:06:02.111
Did you see
the residential-care nurse?

151
00:06:02.112 --> 00:06:03.404
She was out for the Fourth.

152
00:06:03.405 --> 00:06:05.072
but I talked to her
on the phone.

153
00:06:05.073 --> 00:06:07.074
She told me to come here.
and Geri brought me.

154
00:06:07.075 --> 00:06:08.534
- Thank you.
- No problem.

155
00:06:08.535 --> 00:06:10.703
- I'll wait for you.
- Okay.

156
00:06:10.704 --> 00:06:12.538
Okay. Come on. this way.

157
00:06:12.539 --> 00:06:14.373
Uh. just through here.

158
00:06:14.374 --> 00:06:18.085
- Is it always like this?
- Yeah. pretty much.

159
00:06:18.086 --> 00:06:21.463
Wow. There are a lot
of smelly people.

160
00:06:21.464 --> 00:06:22.798
Yeah.

161
00:06:22.799 --> 00:06:24.425
Are you going to help them all?

162
00:06:24.426 --> 00:06:26.594
Yeah. but. um. let's start
with you first.

163
00:06:26.595 --> 00:06:28.178
Okay.

164
00:06:28.179 --> 00:06:31.432
- How's the pain?
- I can't feel my hand anymore.

165
00:06:31.433 --> 00:06:32.975
Ancef's on board.

166
00:06:32.976 --> 00:06:35.311
Okay. we're going to clean
out your hand with saline...

167
00:06:35.312 --> 00:06:37.772
- salt water.
- Okay.

168
00:06:41.568 --> 00:06:43.277
What's up?

169
00:06:43.278 --> 00:06:44.653
Hand versus M-80.

170
00:06:44.654 --> 00:06:46.822
Hmm. Surprised we've only
seen one of these.

171
00:06:46.823 --> 00:06:48.282
The day's still young yet.

172
00:06:48.283 --> 00:06:50.659
Lost fourth metacarpal.
mid-shaft on the fifth.

173
00:06:50.660 --> 00:06:52.912
Bummer.

174
00:06:52.913 --> 00:06:55.164
Hello. I'm Dr. Garcia
from surgery.

175
00:06:55.165 --> 00:06:56.832
- I'm gonna have surgery?
- Yes.

176
00:06:56.833 --> 00:06:59.501
The first operation is to clean
everything up

177
00:06:59.502 --> 00:07:02.004
and cover where the skin
is missing.

178
00:07:02.005 --> 00:07:03.964
But you still have your thumb

179
00:07:03.965 --> 00:07:06.551
and your most important fingers.

180
00:07:09.262 --> 00:07:12.014
- What'd you give him for pain?
- We did regional blocks.

181
00:07:12.015 --> 00:07:14.767
Hand surgery always wants to
document their own neuro exam.

182
00:07:14.768 --> 00:07:17.102
Sensation is intact
to light touch and pinprick

183
00:07:17.103 --> 00:07:19.188
throughout the digits
in the remaining hand.

184
00:07:21.441 --> 00:07:24.360
Um. yeah. FDS and FTPs
and extensor function

185
00:07:24.361 --> 00:07:25.819
was all intact.

186
00:07:25.820 --> 00:07:27.821
Need parental consent
for surgery.

187
00:07:27.822 --> 00:07:30.200
- Yeah. we're working on that.
- Dr. Robby?

188
00:07:33.870 --> 00:07:37.206
I smell alcohol on his breath.

189
00:07:37.207 --> 00:07:38.415
He's in line for the OR.

190
00:07:38.416 --> 00:07:40.000
Might be a little bit of a wait.

191
00:07:40.001 --> 00:07:41.710
Ortho's still in
with Allen Billings...

192
00:07:41.711 --> 00:07:43.837
that open shoulder dislocation
that came back from Westbridge.

193
00:07:43.838 --> 00:07:45.214
He's still in surgery?

194
00:07:45.215 --> 00:07:47.007
He waited an hour
to be cleared by anesthesia.

195
00:07:47.008 --> 00:07:48.342
Is the insurance company

196
00:07:48.343 --> 00:07:50.010
gonna cover the cost
of the surgery?

197
00:07:50.011 --> 00:07:51.512
Yeah. since Westbridge
is still down.

198
00:07:51.513 --> 00:07:53.222
Well. good.
because the delay in care

199
00:07:53.223 --> 00:07:54.974
definitely increased the chance
of a post-op infection.

200
00:07:54.975 --> 00:07:56.850
You got to love it
when insurance companies

201
00:07:56.851 --> 00:07:58.227
make medical decisions.

202
00:07:58.228 --> 00:07:59.603
- Hey.
- What's up?

203
00:07:59.604 --> 00:08:01.355
Do you still need a rain check

204
00:08:01.356 --> 00:08:02.773
for watching fireworks tonight?

205
00:08:02.774 --> 00:08:04.274
I thought you were coming over.

206
00:08:04.275 --> 00:08:07.027
I made other plans.

207
00:08:07.028 --> 00:08:08.529
Okay. cool.

208
00:08:08.530 --> 00:08:10.572
I'll try hitting you up
tomorrow.

209
00:08:10.573 --> 00:08:12.700
We're just keeping
it casual. right?

210
00:08:12.701 --> 00:08:14.035
For sure.

211
00:08:17.372 --> 00:08:19.039
Yeah.

212
00:08:19.040 --> 00:08:21.000
Thank you. Yeah. bye.

213
00:08:21.001 --> 00:08:22.418
Oh. uh. hey.

214
00:08:22.419 --> 00:08:24.503
I just got a hold of the sister
of the heavy patient.

215
00:08:24.504 --> 00:08:26.005
Abbot's taking to Presby.

216
00:08:26.006 --> 00:08:28.257
She still lives in Arizona.
but she is willing to talk

217
00:08:28.258 --> 00:08:29.717
to him when he's back.

218
00:08:29.718 --> 00:08:30.926
That's good news.

219
00:08:30.927 --> 00:08:32.886
When do you think that might be?

220
00:08:32.887 --> 00:08:35.222
Depends on how crazy
it is over at Presby.

221
00:08:35.223 --> 00:08:37.057
If it's anything
like here. who knows?

222
00:08:37.058 --> 00:08:38.392
Yeah.

223
00:08:38.393 --> 00:08:40.060
Um. is help on the way?

224
00:08:40.061 --> 00:08:41.478
Ah. ye of little faith.

225
00:08:41.479 --> 00:08:44.064
You got a gumband?

226
00:08:44.065 --> 00:08:47.276
Thanks. Keep losing these.

227
00:08:47.277 --> 00:08:49.111
Oh. this fucking day.

228
00:08:49.112 --> 00:08:51.613
Thought I was gonna get
a clean getaway for my trip.

229
00:08:51.614 --> 00:08:53.449
God gives His toughest battles

230
00:08:53.450 --> 00:08:54.908
to His strongest soldiers.

231
00:08:54.909 --> 00:08:57.161
- Dana. is there a room open?
- This is my sister.

232
00:08:57.162 --> 00:08:59.413
She's in a lot of pain.
and... and we need a bed ASAP.

233
00:08:59.414 --> 00:09:00.956
My name is Becca.
not "my sister."

234
00:09:00.957 --> 00:09:02.291
Sorry. right.

235
00:09:02.292 --> 00:09:04.710
Um. Dana. Dr. Robby.
this is my...

236
00:09:04.711 --> 00:09:05.961
my... Becca.

237
00:09:05.962 --> 00:09:07.212
Nice to meet you.

238
00:09:07.213 --> 00:09:10.215
You're Dr. Robby? Cool.

239
00:09:10.216 --> 00:09:12.926
- Central 7 was just cleaned.
- Anything I can get you. hon?

240
00:09:12.927 --> 00:09:14.512
No. thank you.

241
00:09:17.098 --> 00:09:19.600
Oh. wait. Becca. Come here.

242
00:09:19.601 --> 00:09:24.146
Come this way.
We're going right in here.

243
00:09:24.147 --> 00:09:27.232
All right. so. um. you're gonna
need to get undressed

244
00:09:27.233 --> 00:09:29.818
and get into the gown.
which should be on the bed.

245
00:09:29.819 --> 00:09:32.529
Then we're gonna do an
evaluation and take a history.

246
00:09:32.530 --> 00:09:34.031
That's a lot of questions.

247
00:09:34.032 --> 00:09:36.116
like. like. a lot. a lot
of questions. which we'll do.

248
00:09:36.117 --> 00:09:37.826
And then a physical exam.
of course.

249
00:09:37.827 --> 00:09:40.162
Mel. I've been
to the doctor's before.

250
00:09:40.163 --> 00:09:42.372
Right. Sorry.

251
00:09:42.373 --> 00:09:45.542
I just... I-I really want this
to be done the right way.

252
00:09:49.798 --> 00:09:51.548
Do you need to take that call?

253
00:09:51.549 --> 00:09:54.009
- Uh. no. it's. um...
- it's a reminder alarm

254
00:09:54.010 --> 00:09:56.553
for this important meeting
I have in 15 minutes.

255
00:09:56.554 --> 00:09:58.764
Um. do you have to go?

256
00:09:58.765 --> 00:10:00.933
Let's just get you
taken care of first. all right?

257
00:10:00.934 --> 00:10:03.769
So just change into the gown.
I'll be behind the curtain.

258
00:10:03.770 --> 00:10:08.149
Okay.

259
00:10:17.826 --> 00:10:20.994
Your grand prize.

260
00:10:20.995 --> 00:10:24.289
All I see is green. baby.

261
00:10:32.215 --> 00:10:34.842
Oh. What's up with her?

262
00:10:34.843 --> 00:10:37.511
- Fax machine has paper jam...
- so annoying.

263
00:10:37.512 --> 00:10:38.972
Hmm.

264
00:10:45.520 --> 00:10:47.855
- You want me to try?
- No.

265
00:10:47.856 --> 00:10:50.232
- Oh. huzzah.
- I got it.

266
00:10:54.529 --> 00:10:56.196
- What's it say?
- "Replace toner."

267
00:10:56.197 --> 00:10:57.531
We live in hell.

268
00:10:57.532 --> 00:10:59.283
- Oh. where can we get that?
- 1988.

269
00:10:59.284 --> 00:11:01.785
- You ever seen one of these?
- Honestly. no.

270
00:11:01.786 --> 00:11:03.745
How are we gonna get labs
and X-rays to the wards?

271
00:11:03.746 --> 00:11:05.539
The old-fashioned way. runners.

272
00:11:05.540 --> 00:11:07.875
I'll check if they
can spare a couple clerks

273
00:11:07.876 --> 00:11:09.419
from upstairs.

274
00:11:13.381 --> 00:11:14.548
When were you first diagnosed

275
00:11:14.549 --> 00:11:16.383
with polycystic ovarian
syndrome?

276
00:11:16.384 --> 00:11:17.718
Last summer.

277
00:11:17.719 --> 00:11:19.553
That's when
the symptoms started?

278
00:11:19.554 --> 00:11:22.222
No. I've had years of pain.
hormonal changes.

279
00:11:22.223 --> 00:11:23.682
and an abnormal period.

280
00:11:23.683 --> 00:11:26.059
I was finally diagnosed
after switching to a gyno

281
00:11:26.060 --> 00:11:27.769
who actually listened to me.

282
00:11:27.770 --> 00:11:31.231
Yeah. it can take time
to make the diagnosis.

283
00:11:31.232 --> 00:11:34.568
That sounds like an excuse
for lazy doctoring.

284
00:11:34.569 --> 00:11:37.571
And it doesn't help that some
of you don't listen to women.

285
00:11:37.572 --> 00:11:39.281
let alone brown ones.

286
00:11:39.282 --> 00:11:40.824
It hasn't been easy.

287
00:11:40.825 --> 00:11:42.993
- How's your pain now?
- Better.

288
00:11:42.994 --> 00:11:45.370
- What was she given?
- IM Toradol.

289
00:11:45.371 --> 00:11:48.582
Have you had a transvaginal
ultrasound before?

290
00:11:48.583 --> 00:11:50.375
I've lost count
of how many times.

291
00:11:50.376 --> 00:11:52.628
Okay. if you want
to scoot your bottom down.

292
00:11:52.629 --> 00:11:55.589
I'll help you put your feet
in the leg rests here.

293
00:11:55.590 --> 00:11:58.091
Yep. you got it.

294
00:12:06.434 --> 00:12:08.435
Okay. ready to go here?

295
00:12:08.436 --> 00:12:11.272
Cold gel and some pressure.

296
00:12:14.108 --> 00:12:16.443
Okay.

297
00:12:16.444 --> 00:12:18.445
Okay. ectopic is unlikely

298
00:12:18.446 --> 00:12:20.781
since the urine pregnancy
was negative.

299
00:12:20.782 --> 00:12:22.824
I'm hoping
it'll be positive one day.

300
00:12:22.825 --> 00:12:25.661
- Oh. are you trying?
- Not at the moment.

301
00:12:25.662 --> 00:12:27.829
I'm getting married
in September.

302
00:12:27.830 --> 00:12:31.124
- Oh. congratulations.
- Okay.

303
00:12:31.125 --> 00:12:34.127
A bunch of small cysts...
to be expected.

304
00:12:34.128 --> 00:12:37.547
But then there's one big one.
about 5 centimeters.

305
00:12:37.548 --> 00:12:39.841
My gyno's been monitoring her.

306
00:12:39.842 --> 00:12:41.134
Mm-hmm.

307
00:12:41.135 --> 00:12:42.552
With a little bit of free fluid.

308
00:12:42.553 --> 00:12:45.180
Checking blood flow
to the ovary.

309
00:12:45.181 --> 00:12:47.641
Red is for artery.
Blue is for vein.

310
00:12:47.642 --> 00:12:49.351
Okay. looks good.

311
00:12:49.352 --> 00:12:51.979
Coming out now.

312
00:12:51.980 --> 00:12:53.898
- Sorry.
- Okay.

313
00:12:55.149 --> 00:12:58.903
We will be back when we get
your blood-test results.

314
00:13:01.322 --> 00:13:02.698
All right. what do you think?

315
00:13:02.699 --> 00:13:04.658
She probably had
a small fluid leak

316
00:13:04.659 --> 00:13:06.493
from the cyst
that caused the pain

317
00:13:06.494 --> 00:13:08.453
that improved
with a nonsteroidal.

318
00:13:08.454 --> 00:13:11.665
- And what's your plan?
- Discharge with naproxen?

319
00:13:11.666 --> 00:13:14.793
Do you think that just might
be what her doctors in the past

320
00:13:14.794 --> 00:13:16.003
have done?

321
00:13:16.004 --> 00:13:17.713
Well. she said
she's feeling better.

322
00:13:17.714 --> 00:13:19.006
We can free up a bed.

323
00:13:19.007 --> 00:13:20.632
Mm. she didn't look good
in triage.

324
00:13:20.633 --> 00:13:23.010
and her pain was way more
severe than previous episodes.

325
00:13:23.011 --> 00:13:25.012
I think we observe her
for a bit.

326
00:13:25.013 --> 00:13:26.638
Okay.

327
00:13:26.639 --> 00:13:30.475
Mr. Green. this is Dr. Mohan
and student doctor Ogilvie.

328
00:13:30.476 --> 00:13:32.644
Uh. what can you tell me
about your flank pain?

329
00:13:32.645 --> 00:13:34.813
Feels like another kidney stone.

330
00:13:34.814 --> 00:13:36.315
You've had them before?

331
00:13:36.316 --> 00:13:38.400
I said "another." which means
an additional thing

332
00:13:38.401 --> 00:13:40.610
of the same type.

333
00:13:40.611 --> 00:13:43.030
I teach English at Point Park.

334
00:13:43.031 --> 00:13:44.281
Triggering.

335
00:13:44.282 --> 00:13:46.700
My dad's a high-school
English teacher.

336
00:13:46.701 --> 00:13:48.118
Oh.

337
00:13:48.119 --> 00:13:51.621
Well. you went into medicine.
He must be really proud.

338
00:13:51.622 --> 00:13:53.373
You'd have to ask him.

339
00:13:53.374 --> 00:13:55.042
Getting back to your pain.

340
00:13:55.043 --> 00:13:57.461
it feels like something
you've experienced before?

341
00:13:57.462 --> 00:13:59.421
Same as always. left kidney.

342
00:13:59.422 --> 00:14:01.423
Started about 10:00 p.m.
last night.

343
00:14:01.424 --> 00:14:03.592
Any fever. blood in the urine?

344
00:14:03.593 --> 00:14:04.926
No. Uh. no fever.

345
00:14:04.927 --> 00:14:06.970
Urine's a bit darker
than normal.

346
00:14:06.971 --> 00:14:08.972
Dehydration can lead
to stone formation.

347
00:14:08.973 --> 00:14:10.557
Lean forward a bit. please.

348
00:14:10.558 --> 00:14:12.893
- Check for CVA tenderness.
- Yeah.

349
00:14:12.894 --> 00:14:14.728
All right.

350
00:14:14.729 --> 00:14:16.897
Let me know if there's
any discomfort.

351
00:14:16.898 --> 00:14:19.733
Mm-hmm.

352
00:14:19.734 --> 00:14:20.734
- Ah!
- Sorry.

353
00:14:20.735 --> 00:14:21.860
Yeah.

354
00:14:21.861 --> 00:14:23.737
We'll order medication
and a few tests.

355
00:14:23.738 --> 00:14:24.822
Okay.

356
00:14:27.617 --> 00:14:29.743
Um. dip urine. Chem Seven.

357
00:14:29.744 --> 00:14:31.745
bedside ultrasound
to check for hydro.

358
00:14:31.746 --> 00:14:33.789
- and ketorolac for pain.
- Sounds good.

359
00:14:33.790 --> 00:14:35.249
Okay.

360
00:14:39.962 --> 00:14:41.588
Really putting me to work.

361
00:14:41.589 --> 00:14:43.673
It's been a very busy day.
Dr. Barker.

362
00:14:43.674 --> 00:14:45.426
Call me Nick.

363
00:14:46.928 --> 00:14:49.679
- What's all this?
- I brought radiology to us.

364
00:14:49.680 --> 00:14:52.391
Dr. Barker. Nick. will have
wet-read results for us

365
00:14:52.392 --> 00:14:53.767
- in no time.
- Good idea.

366
00:14:53.768 --> 00:14:56.019
- Thank you.
- "Wet read"?

367
00:14:56.020 --> 00:14:57.687
You ever take
a photography class?

368
00:14:57.688 --> 00:14:59.147
Yeah. in. like. middle school.

369
00:14:59.148 --> 00:15:00.941
So. before digital
technology. X-ray films

370
00:15:00.942 --> 00:15:03.693
were physically developed
in a darkroom. in baths.

371
00:15:03.694 --> 00:15:05.529
thus wet read.

372
00:15:05.530 --> 00:15:06.655
Oh. cool.

373
00:15:06.656 --> 00:15:09.366
He's taking up a lot of space.

374
00:15:09.367 --> 00:15:11.952
Got an update from Dylan
on our abandoned baby.

375
00:15:11.953 --> 00:15:14.788
CYF has requested an emergency
custody authorization.

376
00:15:14.789 --> 00:15:17.499
Once we get a court order. we
can place her in foster care.

377
00:15:17.500 --> 00:15:20.001
I love photography.

378
00:15:20.002 --> 00:15:21.336
- Jesus Christ.
- Dr. Robby?

379
00:15:21.337 --> 00:15:22.963
Dr. Robby. can I borrow
you for a second?

380
00:15:22.964 --> 00:15:24.297
Sure. What can I do for you?

381
00:15:24.298 --> 00:15:25.966
Well. she said she
has a stomachache.

382
00:15:25.967 --> 00:15:27.926
but belly pain can mean a lot
of different things...

383
00:15:27.927 --> 00:15:30.804
- Okay. okay. okay. breathe.
- I'm looking for Dr. Mel King.

384
00:15:30.805 --> 00:15:32.639
Yes?

385
00:15:32.640 --> 00:15:34.975
I'm Morgan Stiles. one
of the hospital's attorneys.

386
00:15:34.976 --> 00:15:37.769
I'm here to escort you upstairs
for your deposition.

387
00:15:37.770 --> 00:15:39.271
Right now?

388
00:15:39.272 --> 00:15:43.150
Morgan. can I borrow Dr. King
for just a moment?

389
00:15:43.151 --> 00:15:44.485
Sure.

390
00:15:46.154 --> 00:15:47.487
It's gonna be fine.

391
00:15:47.488 --> 00:15:49.531
I can't go up now
because of Becca.

392
00:15:49.532 --> 00:15:51.575
You probably shouldn't be
caring for Becca.

393
00:15:51.576 --> 00:15:53.660
It's not a good idea
to care for family members.

394
00:15:53.661 --> 00:15:55.036
It's hard to stay objective.

395
00:15:55.037 --> 00:15:56.538
Let's see who's available.

396
00:15:56.539 --> 00:15:57.873
Hey. are you free?

397
00:15:57.874 --> 00:16:00.584
Is anybody really free?

398
00:16:00.585 --> 00:16:02.210
Not an R2.

399
00:16:02.211 --> 00:16:04.671
Ah. just the guy
we were looking for.

400
00:16:04.672 --> 00:16:06.089
- Need something?
- Yes.

401
00:16:06.090 --> 00:16:08.049
- Uh-huh. mm-hmm.
- Sure.

402
00:16:08.050 --> 00:16:09.926
Dr. King's sister
has a bellyache.

403
00:16:09.927 --> 00:16:11.178
- The case is now yours.
- Sure.

404
00:16:11.179 --> 00:16:13.054
You can pick up
the rest of her patients

405
00:16:13.055 --> 00:16:14.723
while she's doing
her deposition.

406
00:16:14.724 --> 00:16:16.475
How am I supposed to catch up
on my outstanding charts

407
00:16:16.476 --> 00:16:18.560
with extra patients
and the computer system down?

408
00:16:18.561 --> 00:16:20.395
The same way
that the rest of us do.

409
00:16:20.396 --> 00:16:22.898
You can finish your charting
when you finish your shift.

410
00:16:22.899 --> 00:16:25.026
Fucking fantastic.

411
00:16:29.363 --> 00:16:31.031
- Hi. Becca.
- Hi.

412
00:16:31.032 --> 00:16:32.908
Um. This is Dr. Langdon.

413
00:16:32.909 --> 00:16:34.826
He'll be taking care of you.

414
00:16:34.827 --> 00:16:37.370
You have really nice hair.
Dr. Langdon.

415
00:16:37.371 --> 00:16:39.164
Thank you.

416
00:16:39.165 --> 00:16:42.751
Mel. would you mind turning off
the lights on your way out?

417
00:16:42.752 --> 00:16:44.419
Of course.

418
00:16:44.420 --> 00:16:47.130
And. um. I'll be back
as soon as I'm done.

419
00:16:47.131 --> 00:16:49.132
And feel free to call me
if anything comes up.

420
00:16:49.133 --> 00:16:51.301
- because I can come right...
- Don't... don't worry.

421
00:16:51.302 --> 00:16:54.221
- Becca's in good hands.
- I know.

422
00:16:54.222 --> 00:16:55.556
Okay.

423
00:17:03.189 --> 00:17:06.359
Mel says lots of nice things
about you.

424
00:17:08.319 --> 00:17:09.569
Okay.

425
00:17:09.570 --> 00:17:11.279
Um...

426
00:17:11.280 --> 00:17:13.573
tell me the reason
you're here today.

427
00:17:13.574 --> 00:17:14.950
I have a stomachache.

428
00:17:14.951 --> 00:17:16.743
Your belly hurts? Where about?

429
00:17:16.744 --> 00:17:19.913
- Right. um... right down here.
- Okay.

430
00:17:19.914 --> 00:17:21.957
Are you experiencing
anything else.

431
00:17:21.958 --> 00:17:23.792
or is it just the stomachache?

432
00:17:23.793 --> 00:17:25.794
It... it stings when I pee.

433
00:17:25.795 --> 00:17:27.879
Sometimes when that happens.

434
00:17:27.880 --> 00:17:30.590
women feel like they need
to urinate all the time.

435
00:17:30.591 --> 00:17:32.384
- Do you feel that way?
- Yes.

436
00:17:32.385 --> 00:17:34.135
And what happens when you go?

437
00:17:34.136 --> 00:17:36.888
Hardly anything comes out.

438
00:17:36.889 --> 00:17:38.431
That's what I thought.

439
00:17:38.432 --> 00:17:40.934
Really? How do you know?

440
00:17:40.935 --> 00:17:42.602
Well. I've seen
a lot of patients

441
00:17:42.603 --> 00:17:44.980
- with the same symptoms.
- So this is normal?

442
00:17:44.981 --> 00:17:46.648
Yes. it's totally normal.

443
00:17:46.649 --> 00:17:49.109
But we still need to fix it.

444
00:17:49.110 --> 00:17:50.611
Okay.

445
00:17:56.284 --> 00:17:57.450
Hey.

446
00:17:57.451 --> 00:17:59.703
How's it going. Roxy?

447
00:17:59.704 --> 00:18:01.955
- A little better.
- Yeah?

448
00:18:01.956 --> 00:18:04.000
You need more morphine?

449
00:18:09.505 --> 00:18:13.216
I've been in pain
all this time. my love.

450
00:18:13.217 --> 00:18:15.343
Why didn't you tell me?

451
00:18:15.344 --> 00:18:18.639
I didn't want you guys to worry.

452
00:18:20.266 --> 00:18:23.310
I can't pretend anymore.

453
00:18:23.311 --> 00:18:26.980
Mom. it's so hot outside.
the ice cream's melting.

454
00:18:26.981 --> 00:18:29.816
We. uh...

455
00:18:29.817 --> 00:18:33.111
we thought we'd indulge a bit.

456
00:18:33.112 --> 00:18:35.030
- Oh. yeah.
- Ooh.

457
00:18:35.031 --> 00:18:36.448
Looks amazing.

458
00:18:36.449 --> 00:18:38.992
So. uh. which flavor
should we start with?

459
00:18:38.993 --> 00:18:42.162
Salty caramel. Mom's favorite.

460
00:18:42.163 --> 00:18:44.665
You'll need lots more napkins.

461
00:18:47.001 --> 00:18:48.835
Mmm.

462
00:18:58.846 --> 00:19:01.515
{\an8}Rude.

463
00:19:03.601 --> 00:19:05.727
- How's it going in there?
- All good.

464
00:19:05.728 --> 00:19:07.187
Langdon's great with her.

465
00:19:07.188 --> 00:19:09.105
I got seven more films
ordered. waiting to be shot.

466
00:19:09.106 --> 00:19:11.566
but Dr. Nick here's tying up
the machine.

467
00:19:11.567 --> 00:19:14.277
Isn't there a USB port
on the front of that portable?

468
00:19:14.278 --> 00:19:17.113
And can't we just download
the films to a workstation

469
00:19:17.114 --> 00:19:18.865
and watch them
without the Internet?

470
00:19:18.866 --> 00:19:20.784
- Yes.
- Oh. right. Forgot about that.

471
00:19:20.785 --> 00:19:23.495
Is he actually helping.
or is he just distracting?

472
00:19:23.496 --> 00:19:25.372
Let's download these
and start moving on to folks

473
00:19:25.373 --> 00:19:27.415
- waiting for X-rays.
- Great. I'm caught up anyway.

474
00:19:27.416 --> 00:19:29.167
I'll be back
when the next batch is ready.

475
00:19:29.168 --> 00:19:31.336
Dr. Robby. the guardian
of your missing-fingers kid

476
00:19:31.337 --> 00:19:33.380
- in Central 12 has arrived.
- Thank you. Olive.

477
00:19:33.381 --> 00:19:35.548
Will you ask Dr. Santos
to come and meet me. too?

478
00:19:35.549 --> 00:19:37.050
- On it.
- Who's in South 22?

479
00:19:37.051 --> 00:19:38.677
- Nobody.
- Headache was discharged.

480
00:19:38.678 --> 00:19:40.428
Tell that
to the lady on the bed.

481
00:19:40.429 --> 00:19:41.888
What lady?

482
00:19:41.889 --> 00:19:44.015
I just tried to put
a hematuria patient in there.

483
00:19:44.016 --> 00:19:46.226
- but. uh. it's occupied.
- South 22? You sure?

484
00:19:46.227 --> 00:19:48.061
- I'm positive.
- That's my patient.

485
00:19:48.062 --> 00:19:50.271
Then why isn't she on the board?

486
00:19:50.272 --> 00:19:51.690
I... She should be.

487
00:19:51.691 --> 00:19:53.441
Olive was bringing her back
from triage.

488
00:19:53.442 --> 00:19:54.901
I picked her right up.

489
00:19:54.902 --> 00:19:56.403
I just assumed
she made it to the board.

490
00:19:56.404 --> 00:19:57.987
- You should've checked.
- You should've made sure.

491
00:19:57.988 --> 00:19:59.656
I-I haven't put anybody
on the board.

492
00:19:59.657 --> 00:20:01.783
- I thought the nurses did that.
- We all need to pitch in.

493
00:20:01.784 --> 00:20:03.743
There's no rooms at the moment.
Put hematuria on the wall.

494
00:20:03.744 --> 00:20:06.287
- Who's your patient?
- Mrs. Burns. with nausea.

495
00:20:06.288 --> 00:20:08.248
- I've ordered labs and X-rays.
- Who are you seeing her with?

496
00:20:08.249 --> 00:20:09.708
I still need
to present the case.

497
00:20:09.709 --> 00:20:12.962
Get busy. Find somebody
with MD after their name.

498
00:20:14.588 --> 00:20:17.340
Oh. God. kids.

499
00:20:17.341 --> 00:20:20.135
Hello. I'm Dr. Robby.

500
00:20:20.136 --> 00:20:21.720
This is Dr. Santos.

501
00:20:21.721 --> 00:20:23.179
- Chantal.
- How do you do?

502
00:20:23.180 --> 00:20:24.556
We've been caring
for your brother.

503
00:20:24.557 --> 00:20:26.266
Are you Jude's legal guardian?

504
00:20:26.267 --> 00:20:27.434
Yeah.

505
00:20:27.435 --> 00:20:29.936
Our. uh... our parents
aren't around.

506
00:20:29.937 --> 00:20:32.313
- Is he going to be okay?
- He got very lucky.

507
00:20:32.314 --> 00:20:34.149
He lost the fourth
and fifth fingers

508
00:20:34.150 --> 00:20:35.650
on his nondominant hand.

509
00:20:35.651 --> 00:20:37.110
But if he hadn't dropped
the firecracker.

510
00:20:37.111 --> 00:20:38.445
it would have been a lot worse.

511
00:20:38.446 --> 00:20:41.114
He lost fingers
from a firecracker?

512
00:20:41.115 --> 00:20:43.158
Will he be able to use his hand?

513
00:20:43.159 --> 00:20:45.785
Yes. he still has his
three most important fingers.

514
00:20:45.786 --> 00:20:47.328
and they are fully functional.

515
00:20:47.329 --> 00:20:49.414
He'll need surgery
to clean everything up.

516
00:20:49.415 --> 00:20:50.957
but it should heal well.

517
00:20:50.958 --> 00:20:53.126
What the fuck were you thinking?

518
00:20:53.127 --> 00:20:54.127
I'm sorry.

519
00:20:54.128 --> 00:20:55.795
Alex asked me to come over.

520
00:20:55.796 --> 00:20:58.006
{\an8}His brother had
a stack of fire...

521
00:21:01.343 --> 00:21:03.303
You think I wanted
to blow my hand off?

522
00:21:03.304 --> 00:21:05.555
Then you need to listen to me
when I tell you something.

523
00:21:05.556 --> 00:21:06.806
You're not my mom.

524
00:21:06.807 --> 00:21:08.308
You think I want to be your mom?

525
00:21:08.309 --> 00:21:11.144
Chantal. why don't
we take a step outside?

526
00:21:13.898 --> 00:21:16.649
So I know that this can be
very stressful.

527
00:21:16.650 --> 00:21:18.651
Yeah. he almost lost
his hand being stupid.

528
00:21:18.652 --> 00:21:20.737
- He's a really sweet kid.
- He used to be.

529
00:21:20.738 --> 00:21:22.989
We also found something
in his blood work.

530
00:21:22.990 --> 00:21:24.240
What?

531
00:21:24.241 --> 00:21:26.701
He has a blood alcohol of 0.08.

532
00:21:26.702 --> 00:21:29.788
What. he was drunk?

533
00:21:29.789 --> 00:21:31.456
Are you fucking kidding me?

534
00:21:31.457 --> 00:21:34.042
- Does he drink regularly?
- No.

535
00:21:34.043 --> 00:21:37.003
I... I don't know. I...

536
00:21:37.004 --> 00:21:39.047
The boys
at our apartment complex

537
00:21:39.048 --> 00:21:40.882
are a really bad influence.

538
00:21:40.883 --> 00:21:42.133
I mean. he's only 12.

539
00:21:42.134 --> 00:21:44.010
That is what concerns us.

540
00:21:44.011 --> 00:21:45.345
A positive blood alcohol

541
00:21:45.346 --> 00:21:47.347
immediately triggers
a social service consult.

542
00:21:47.348 --> 00:21:48.890
They gonna take
my brother away from me?

543
00:21:48.891 --> 00:21:50.683
It's an evaluation
to determine if the injury

544
00:21:50.684 --> 00:21:52.852
and the drinking is cause
for some kind of intervention.

545
00:21:52.853 --> 00:21:55.688
Whoa. whoa.
I won't let you separate us.

546
00:21:55.689 --> 00:21:57.775
- We are required to...
- No!

547
00:22:04.740 --> 00:22:05.865
Hmm.

548
00:22:05.866 --> 00:22:07.534
58-year-old woman with nausea.

549
00:22:07.535 --> 00:22:09.786
vomited once after eating warm
potato salad at a barbecue.

550
00:22:09.787 --> 00:22:11.538
Well-hydrated...
abdomen's pretty benign.

551
00:22:11.539 --> 00:22:13.790
just a little distended
with mild tenderness.

552
00:22:13.791 --> 00:22:16.000
History of constipation.
I give her Zofran.

553
00:22:16.001 --> 00:22:17.794
Labs and abdominal
series pending.

554
00:22:17.795 --> 00:22:20.046
- Okay. let's take a look.
- Okay.

555
00:22:20.047 --> 00:22:21.339
Hi. Mrs. Burns.

556
00:22:21.340 --> 00:22:24.217
This is Dr. Whitaker.
How are you feeling?

557
00:22:24.218 --> 00:22:26.219
Mrs. Burns?

558
00:22:26.220 --> 00:22:28.429
Mrs. Burns. can you open
your eyes for me?

559
00:22:28.430 --> 00:22:30.390
She was awake and alert
last time I saw her.

560
00:22:30.391 --> 00:22:33.059
Okay. uh. feels warm.
thready pulse.

561
00:22:33.060 --> 00:22:34.894
Abdomen's more distended
than before.

562
00:22:34.895 --> 00:22:37.021
Okay. uh. agonal respirations.

563
00:22:37.022 --> 00:22:39.023
- She's... she's hardly breathing.
- It's kind of rigid.

564
00:22:39.024 --> 00:22:41.192
Yeah. yeah. Perlah.
we need a crash cart.

565
00:22:41.193 --> 00:22:42.694
Can you call respiratory?

566
00:22:42.695 --> 00:22:44.904
Pull the bed out
for intubation. please.

567
00:22:44.905 --> 00:22:47.115
I can give you guys some room.

568
00:22:47.116 --> 00:22:48.616
- Okay.
- What's up?

569
00:22:48.617 --> 00:22:51.077
- Hypotensive. acute abdomen.
- She needs an airway.

570
00:22:51.078 --> 00:22:53.246
- I'll find the GlideScope.
- No time for that.

571
00:22:53.247 --> 00:22:54.747
We've got direct
on the crash cart.

572
00:22:54.748 --> 00:22:56.708
- Whitaker. you're up.
- I haven't done many directs.

573
00:22:56.709 --> 00:22:58.126
Well. then you need to do more.

574
00:22:58.127 --> 00:23:00.086
- Induction meds?
- 100 ketamine. 80 of raw.

575
00:23:00.087 --> 00:23:02.630
Javadi. what's the story?

576
00:23:02.631 --> 00:23:04.591
Presented
with mild abdominal pain.

577
00:23:04.592 --> 00:23:07.510
took a turn for the worse.

578
00:23:07.511 --> 00:23:10.263
A-fib 122. BP 98 and systolic.

579
00:23:10.264 --> 00:23:11.806
Okay. let's bolus
another 500 cc's.

580
00:23:11.807 --> 00:23:14.267
- Are we shocking her?
- Uh. maybe. After intubation.

581
00:23:14.268 --> 00:23:15.852
Check your light.
Check your balloon.

582
00:23:15.853 --> 00:23:17.937
Javadi. AP pads in case
we need to cardiovert.

583
00:23:17.938 --> 00:23:20.189
- Normal EKG at triage.
- She wasn't in A-fib.

584
00:23:20.190 --> 00:23:22.609
Stress from her condition
probably put her there.

585
00:23:22.610 --> 00:23:23.985
Good? Let's roll her.

586
00:23:23.986 --> 00:23:26.321
- Do we have any labs back?
- I don't think so.

587
00:23:26.322 --> 00:23:28.656
- What else do we need?
- Um. blood cultures.

588
00:23:28.657 --> 00:23:31.159
Lactate. 2 liters LR.
3.375 pip-tazo.

589
00:23:31.160 --> 00:23:32.410
Okay. she's loose.

590
00:23:32.411 --> 00:23:34.621
Go ahead. Whitaker. Take a look.

591
00:23:34.622 --> 00:23:37.875
Okay.

592
00:23:42.630 --> 00:23:45.506
- Hi. I'm Dr. Santos.
- This is student doctor Kwon.

593
00:23:45.507 --> 00:23:47.133
How are you doing
after the mist?

594
00:23:47.134 --> 00:23:48.843
Better than I was an hour ago.

595
00:23:48.844 --> 00:23:52.639
Okay. we are going
to check your vitals.

596
00:23:53.807 --> 00:23:58.269
Temp is 100.2.
and heart rate is 96.

597
00:23:58.270 --> 00:24:00.688
Okay. down from 101.5 and 120.

598
00:24:00.689 --> 00:24:02.231
Very good.

599
00:24:02.232 --> 00:24:04.567
You were out in the heat
in that costume?

600
00:24:04.568 --> 00:24:07.528
Yeah. with about 18.000
of my friends.

601
00:24:07.529 --> 00:24:09.822
- Were you at Anthrocon?
- Uh-huh.

602
00:24:09.823 --> 00:24:11.199
What's that?

603
00:24:11.200 --> 00:24:13.242
Pittsburgh's annual
furry convention.

604
00:24:13.243 --> 00:24:14.827
I go every year.

605
00:24:14.828 --> 00:24:16.496
Ever been?

606
00:24:16.497 --> 00:24:19.332
- Uh. it's not really my scene.
- Mm.

607
00:24:19.333 --> 00:24:20.750
Yeah. furries get a bad rap.

608
00:24:20.751 --> 00:24:23.711
but there are great people
in the community...

609
00:24:23.712 --> 00:24:27.215
creative. welcoming. funny.

610
00:24:27.216 --> 00:24:30.009
I actually met my girlfriend
at last year's convention.

611
00:24:30.010 --> 00:24:31.636
Oh. that's cute.

612
00:24:31.637 --> 00:24:34.472
She gave me hope after
struggling on the dating apps.

613
00:24:34.473 --> 00:24:35.723
Nice to hear

614
00:24:35.724 --> 00:24:38.184
that meeting people
in real life still works.

615
00:24:38.185 --> 00:24:40.979
Wouldn't recommend it.
especially at work.

616
00:24:40.980 --> 00:24:44.023
You should come
to Anthrocon this weekend.

617
00:24:44.024 --> 00:24:46.484
Doesn't she need
a fur suit for that?

618
00:24:46.485 --> 00:24:49.029
I think you'd make
a good dragon.

619
00:24:52.324 --> 00:24:53.700
I'm in.

620
00:24:53.701 --> 00:24:54.993
Balloon up.

621
00:24:54.994 --> 00:24:57.704
Yep. bag her.

622
00:24:57.705 --> 00:24:59.330
Okay.

623
00:24:59.331 --> 00:25:02.208
- That was harder without video.
- We won't always have video.

624
00:25:02.209 --> 00:25:03.376
A-fib now at 152.

625
00:25:03.377 --> 00:25:05.253
Blood pressure's
down to 76 over 44.

626
00:25:05.254 --> 00:25:09.424
- Okay. Javadi. sync mode.
- Javadi. sync mode. 200. please.

627
00:25:09.425 --> 00:25:11.384
Good end tidal waveform.

628
00:25:11.385 --> 00:25:13.720
Good breath sounds bilaterally.

629
00:25:13.721 --> 00:25:16.264
Charged for cardioversion.

630
00:25:16.265 --> 00:25:18.808
Everyone. clear.

631
00:25:20.978 --> 00:25:23.896
- Normal sinus.
- Normal radial pulse.

632
00:25:25.232 --> 00:25:26.983
Good. Keep the fluids going.

633
00:25:26.984 --> 00:25:29.486
Let's see what labs
are back on her.

634
00:25:31.321 --> 00:25:32.447
Nice.

635
00:25:32.448 --> 00:25:35.116
Very nice.

636
00:25:35.117 --> 00:25:38.202
- What did you order?
- Um. CBC. ER chem panel.

637
00:25:38.203 --> 00:25:40.788
- Something should be back.
- Fax machine ran out of toner.

638
00:25:40.789 --> 00:25:43.416
- Check the chart.
- There is no chart in slot 22.

639
00:25:43.417 --> 00:25:45.918
Check the orders rack.

640
00:25:45.919 --> 00:25:47.462
Nothing here either.

641
00:25:47.463 --> 00:25:49.923
Where's the chart
for Claire Burns?

642
00:25:51.800 --> 00:25:53.259
Claire Burns. order slip.

643
00:25:53.260 --> 00:25:54.927
Never drawn.
never sent off to the lab.

644
00:25:54.928 --> 00:25:56.637
That's cause the patient
wasn't on the board.

645
00:25:56.638 --> 00:25:58.222
Nurses are working zones.

646
00:25:58.223 --> 00:25:59.974
If the patient's not
on the board. they don't exist.

647
00:25:59.975 --> 00:26:01.601
So they didn't shoot her X-ray?

648
00:26:01.602 --> 00:26:03.936
- X-ray downtime box is empty.
- That means it was done.

649
00:26:03.937 --> 00:26:05.646
Then it's
on the portable machine.

650
00:26:05.647 --> 00:26:07.940
Last I saw. it was headed north.

651
00:26:07.941 --> 00:26:09.817
- Thanks. Dana.
- Yep.

652
00:26:09.818 --> 00:26:11.694
Hey. Kenny.
can you wait up a sec?

653
00:26:11.695 --> 00:26:13.154
If you need an X-ray.
write the order.

654
00:26:13.155 --> 00:26:14.363
Fill out a downtime.

655
00:26:14.364 --> 00:26:16.115
Did you shoot a KUB in South 22?

656
00:26:16.116 --> 00:26:17.450
No. Maybe another tech did?

657
00:26:17.451 --> 00:26:19.118
Okay. can you flick
through the films.

658
00:26:19.119 --> 00:26:21.121
look for a patient... Burns?

659
00:26:24.500 --> 00:26:25.750
Oh. shit.

660
00:26:25.751 --> 00:26:27.627
Oh. that is a classic
sigmoid volvulus.

661
00:26:27.628 --> 00:26:29.629
- Peritoneal signs.
- Okay. call the OR.

662
00:26:29.630 --> 00:26:32.466
She's going to need
surgery ASAP.

663
00:26:39.640 --> 00:26:41.766
Urine shows three plus blood.

664
00:26:41.767 --> 00:26:43.643
No surprise.

665
00:26:43.644 --> 00:26:45.686
BUN and creatinine are normal.

666
00:26:45.687 --> 00:26:47.355
No evidence
of renal insufficiency.

667
00:26:47.356 --> 00:26:49.148
I got a good look
at the left kidney...

668
00:26:49.149 --> 00:26:52.318
mild hydronephrosis consistent
with ureteral column.

669
00:26:52.319 --> 00:26:54.612
How was the rest
of the ultrasound?

670
00:26:54.613 --> 00:26:57.949
Normal. Uh. Pain improved
after 15 ketorolac IM.

671
00:26:57.950 --> 00:27:00.660
Now you can give
another 15 and observe.

672
00:27:00.661 --> 00:27:03.287
Hmm.

673
00:27:03.288 --> 00:27:05.999
Just need you
to cosign my order.

674
00:27:07.835 --> 00:27:09.001
Thank you.

675
00:27:09.002 --> 00:27:11.712
Something on your mind?

676
00:27:11.713 --> 00:27:14.340
Yeah. I-I saw this regular
an hour ago.

677
00:27:14.341 --> 00:27:16.092
He's in his 60s.
fakes an ailment

678
00:27:16.093 --> 00:27:18.553
so he can come in to chat
every now and then

679
00:27:18.554 --> 00:27:20.263
because he's really lonely.

680
00:27:20.264 --> 00:27:22.431
You sure he just doesn't have
a crush on you?

681
00:27:22.432 --> 00:27:25.226
Maybe. but it got me thinking
about my mom.

682
00:27:25.227 --> 00:27:27.937
She's probably just been lonely.

683
00:27:27.938 --> 00:27:30.106
Yeah.

684
00:27:30.107 --> 00:27:31.566
You know. I. uh...

685
00:27:31.567 --> 00:27:34.235
I haven't really dated
since my divorce.

686
00:27:34.236 --> 00:27:36.571
Medical school.
my kid. residency.

687
00:27:36.572 --> 00:27:39.198
And now I'm feeling
finally kind of ready.

688
00:27:39.199 --> 00:27:41.200
I was waiting
until I got back to Jersey

689
00:27:41.201 --> 00:27:43.035
to work on finding
a relationship.

690
00:27:43.036 --> 00:27:44.579
and now that's out the window.

691
00:27:44.580 --> 00:27:46.747
Maybe I waited too long.

692
00:27:46.748 --> 00:27:47.915
For what?

693
00:27:47.916 --> 00:27:49.709
Do you hear that?

694
00:27:49.710 --> 00:27:54.046
That painful. lonely silence
is the sound of my eggs dying.

695
00:27:56.842 --> 00:27:58.176
Ah.

696
00:27:58.177 --> 00:28:00.219
So the rash in North 3
has been discharged.

697
00:28:00.220 --> 00:28:02.096
The Tasered law student
in Central 10

698
00:28:02.097 --> 00:28:03.389
has gone up to psych.

699
00:28:03.390 --> 00:28:05.183
The eye stroke is
now in the ICU.

700
00:28:05.184 --> 00:28:06.893
And the tongue laceration
in South 15

701
00:28:06.894 --> 00:28:08.519
is sobering up
before we discharge.

702
00:28:08.520 --> 00:28:10.396
which better be soon
because we need the room.

703
00:28:10.397 --> 00:28:11.606
Okay. I'll grab a med student

704
00:28:11.607 --> 00:28:13.107
and get more patients
moving out.

705
00:28:13.108 --> 00:28:15.067
You're not fazed
by any of this chaos?

706
00:28:15.068 --> 00:28:17.069
- Hmm.
- What a fucking mess.

707
00:28:17.070 --> 00:28:20.072
Jesus Christ. we need you.

708
00:28:20.073 --> 00:28:23.576
Monica Peters. this is our new
attending. Dr. Al-Hashimi.

709
00:28:23.577 --> 00:28:25.328
- Welcome.
- Thank you.

710
00:28:25.329 --> 00:28:27.413
Monica's a retired clerk.
best of the best.

711
00:28:27.414 --> 00:28:29.415
She was kind enough
to come in on a holiday

712
00:28:29.416 --> 00:28:31.000
and help get us back into shape.

713
00:28:31.001 --> 00:28:32.835
Laid off
by the digital revolution.

714
00:28:32.836 --> 00:28:34.462
- not retired.
- Okay.

715
00:28:34.463 --> 00:28:37.089
And how's all this digital
shit working out for you now?

716
00:28:37.090 --> 00:28:39.300
- Not so good.
- Exactly.

717
00:28:39.301 --> 00:28:41.177
All right. then. who's handling

718
00:28:41.178 --> 00:28:43.638
- the charts and the orders?
- That's us. right here.

719
00:28:43.639 --> 00:28:45.431
How long have you been clerks?

720
00:28:45.432 --> 00:28:47.892
- Uh. just today.
- We're medical assistants.

721
00:28:47.893 --> 00:28:49.227
Then get out of my space

722
00:28:49.228 --> 00:28:51.479
and go do something
you know how to do.

723
00:28:51.480 --> 00:28:52.813
And no personal calls.

724
00:28:52.814 --> 00:28:54.774
Red phones are
for emergencies only.

725
00:28:54.775 --> 00:28:56.609
This is a hospital.
for God's sake.

726
00:28:56.610 --> 00:28:57.652
I'll call you back.

727
00:28:57.653 --> 00:28:58.986
- Got a gumband?
- Yeah.

728
00:28:58.987 --> 00:29:00.780
Hi. I'm Makedah
from admin and records.

729
00:29:00.781 --> 00:29:02.823
I have a new badge
for a Dr. Whitaker.

730
00:29:02.824 --> 00:29:04.909
Yeah. I'll get that to him.

731
00:29:04.910 --> 00:29:06.661
Heard you all
need extra runners?

732
00:29:06.662 --> 00:29:08.621
- Perfect timing.
- How fast can you move?

733
00:29:08.622 --> 00:29:10.289
- I run marathons.
- Great.

734
00:29:10.290 --> 00:29:13.167
Grab the blood samples and the
bin and get them up to the lab.

735
00:29:13.168 --> 00:29:15.628
I want a lab run
every 15 minutes.

736
00:29:15.629 --> 00:29:17.129
Got it.

737
00:29:22.302 --> 00:29:24.387
I work at a shoe store
in Oakland.

738
00:29:24.388 --> 00:29:26.389
Full-time and you're in school?

739
00:29:26.390 --> 00:29:27.974
Yes. and. yes.

740
00:29:27.975 --> 00:29:29.642
Allegheny Community.

741
00:29:29.643 --> 00:29:31.978
Does Jude go
to summer school or camp

742
00:29:31.979 --> 00:29:35.982
while you're
at. uh. work or school?

743
00:29:35.983 --> 00:29:37.984
Can't afford it.

744
00:29:37.985 --> 00:29:39.568
Are there any other
family members

745
00:29:39.569 --> 00:29:41.988
that could help with his care
when you're not available?

746
00:29:41.989 --> 00:29:43.323
No.

747
00:29:46.493 --> 00:29:47.827
Chantal. we want to help you.

748
00:29:47.828 --> 00:29:50.454
but we can't help
if you won't talk to us.

749
00:29:50.455 --> 00:29:52.540
What. you're
gonna take Jude away

750
00:29:52.541 --> 00:29:54.333
and put him in foster care?

751
00:29:54.334 --> 00:29:57.378
I promised my parents
that would never happen.

752
00:29:57.379 --> 00:29:59.714
Did your parents pass away?

753
00:29:59.715 --> 00:30:01.173
Nope.

754
00:30:01.174 --> 00:30:04.720
What happened to them?

755
00:30:09.224 --> 00:30:12.643
My parents were deported
to Haiti nine months ago.

756
00:30:15.188 --> 00:30:18.232
They went in for their
immigration hearing and were...

757
00:30:18.233 --> 00:30:20.526
detained.

758
00:30:20.527 --> 00:30:22.445
I was a sophomore at Ithaca.

759
00:30:22.446 --> 00:30:26.115
I had to move back home
to take care of my brother.

760
00:30:26.116 --> 00:30:27.783
I'm sorry.

761
00:30:27.784 --> 00:30:32.413
It was either that. or he
moved back to Haiti with them.

762
00:30:32.414 --> 00:30:34.957
He's never been there.

763
00:30:34.958 --> 00:30:37.377
We were both born here.

764
00:30:39.046 --> 00:30:43.424
My mom was so excited
when I got into college.

765
00:30:43.425 --> 00:30:45.551
She worked so hard

766
00:30:45.552 --> 00:30:48.554
to save up and pay my tuition.

767
00:30:48.555 --> 00:30:50.556
And now all she wants

768
00:30:50.557 --> 00:30:52.976
is for my brother
to finish high school.

769
00:30:54.895 --> 00:30:57.021
Man. being a big sister's
a lot easier

770
00:30:57.022 --> 00:30:58.982
than being a surrogate mom.

771
00:31:01.568 --> 00:31:03.361
Just give us a moment. please.

772
00:31:03.362 --> 00:31:05.822
and I'll come grab you
when we're done.

773
00:31:09.284 --> 00:31:11.869
Do we really need to get
family services involved?

774
00:31:11.870 --> 00:31:13.913
You wanted to get
them involved this morning

775
00:31:13.914 --> 00:31:16.123
with your eight-year-old
ITP patient.

776
00:31:16.124 --> 00:31:18.751
- That's different.
- Abuse trumps neglect.

777
00:31:18.752 --> 00:31:20.669
We can't separate her
from her brother.

778
00:31:20.670 --> 00:31:22.254
It's not right.

779
00:31:22.255 --> 00:31:25.008
A lot of what happens to
people around here isn't right.

780
00:31:29.679 --> 00:31:32.765
McKay. patient's
complaining of pain.

781
00:31:32.766 --> 00:31:35.601
Uh. yeah.

782
00:31:35.602 --> 00:31:38.354
Hey. Amaya. What's going on?

783
00:31:38.355 --> 00:31:40.147
Oh. it really
fucking hurts again.

784
00:31:40.148 --> 00:31:42.149
Hey. Jesse.
can you grab Whitaker?

785
00:31:42.150 --> 00:31:44.693
- When did it get bad?
- Two minutes ago. Aah!

786
00:31:44.694 --> 00:31:46.779
Giving you some morphine
to take the edge off.

787
00:31:46.780 --> 00:31:50.282
- How severe. 1 to 10?
- Ah. 12. It's way worse.

788
00:31:50.283 --> 00:31:51.617
Okay.

789
00:31:51.618 --> 00:31:53.619
Hey. Amaya. the meds
will kick in.

790
00:31:53.620 --> 00:31:55.579
and we'll get you back
on the foot rest

791
00:31:55.580 --> 00:31:58.749
to see what's going on. okay?

792
00:32:01.461 --> 00:32:04.964
I had to call her husband
in New York to get consent.

793
00:32:04.965 --> 00:32:06.006
Okay.

794
00:32:06.007 --> 00:32:08.467
Dr. Shamsi will be operating.

795
00:32:08.468 --> 00:32:10.469
If she presented
with peritoneal signs.

796
00:32:10.470 --> 00:32:12.096
why wasn't I called?

797
00:32:12.097 --> 00:32:14.807
There was
a delayed presentation.

798
00:32:14.808 --> 00:32:16.475
The X-ray was shot an hour ago.

799
00:32:16.476 --> 00:32:18.018
Why didn't anybody read it?

800
00:32:18.019 --> 00:32:19.979
There was confusion
with the digital systems down.

801
00:32:19.980 --> 00:32:21.647
It wasn't read.
We didn't get a report.

802
00:32:21.648 --> 00:32:24.358
An hour ago. I could have
fixed this in 60 seconds

803
00:32:24.359 --> 00:32:25.985
with a rectal tube.

804
00:32:25.986 --> 00:32:27.653
Now she needs major surgery.

805
00:32:27.654 --> 00:32:30.531
- I'm sorry.
- Not good enough. nepo baby.

806
00:32:30.532 --> 00:32:32.116
You fucked up.

807
00:32:32.117 --> 00:32:34.660
Don't trust anything or anybody
else when the system's down.

808
00:32:36.163 --> 00:32:39.666
With all the chaos. she
just fell through the cracks.

809
00:32:41.251 --> 00:32:44.086
She almost died.

810
00:32:44.087 --> 00:32:45.838
I could have killed her.

811
00:32:45.839 --> 00:32:47.673
- Whitaker.
- No...

812
00:32:47.674 --> 00:32:50.176
McKay needs you in Central 11.

813
00:32:50.177 --> 00:32:51.844
We caught it in time.

814
00:32:51.845 --> 00:32:54.347
We won't let it
happen again. okay?

815
00:33:05.692 --> 00:33:08.235
Oh. uh. Princess
is looking for you.

816
00:33:08.236 --> 00:33:11.405
Um. she said something
about Monica under her breath.

817
00:33:11.406 --> 00:33:14.867
- but I couldn't make it out.
- Okay. I'll be back in a sec.

818
00:33:14.868 --> 00:33:17.703
Hey. Hey.

819
00:33:17.704 --> 00:33:21.415
You did good with that
sexual-assault victim.

820
00:33:21.416 --> 00:33:23.542
You were amazing with her.

821
00:33:23.543 --> 00:33:25.628
We do what we can to provide
the best care

822
00:33:25.629 --> 00:33:29.048
to traumatized people
in their darkest days.

823
00:33:29.049 --> 00:33:30.466
What'd you talk to her about

824
00:33:30.467 --> 00:33:32.468
when you took her out
on the walk?

825
00:33:32.469 --> 00:33:34.637
I. um...

826
00:33:34.638 --> 00:33:36.639
told her there might be a time
in the future

827
00:33:36.640 --> 00:33:41.560
when she changes her mind.
wants to press charges.

828
00:33:41.561 --> 00:33:44.438
It's better to have
the option to do it than not.

829
00:33:44.439 --> 00:33:46.733
Smart.

830
00:33:48.777 --> 00:33:50.402
Is every day like this?

831
00:33:50.403 --> 00:33:54.573
Minus the cyberattacks. yeah.

832
00:33:54.574 --> 00:33:56.575
But you're only a few hours away

833
00:33:56.576 --> 00:33:59.245
from being done
with your first of many.

834
00:33:59.246 --> 00:34:00.621
Be proud of that.

835
00:34:07.587 --> 00:34:09.713
You're gonna want to be
on a soft diet.

836
00:34:09.714 --> 00:34:12.800
so. uh. things
like. uh. mashed potatoes.

837
00:34:12.801 --> 00:34:14.885
soup. mac and cheese are good.

838
00:34:14.886 --> 00:34:16.428
I was gonna make

839
00:34:16.429 --> 00:34:18.305
your favorite
three-bean dip tonight.

840
00:34:18.306 --> 00:34:20.266
Bitch. that is so nice.

841
00:34:20.267 --> 00:34:21.642
See. I am nice.

842
00:34:21.643 --> 00:34:23.394
Could she have that?

843
00:34:23.395 --> 00:34:26.355
Uh. yeah. Yeah. yeah.
if you eat it with a spoon

844
00:34:26.356 --> 00:34:28.107
rather than anything.
like. crunchy

845
00:34:28.108 --> 00:34:30.276
that could work its way
into the laceration.

846
00:34:30.277 --> 00:34:31.277
Mm.

847
00:34:31.278 --> 00:34:33.028
So she'll need to be spoon-fed?

848
00:34:34.322 --> 00:34:36.323
Antibiotics three times a day.

849
00:34:36.324 --> 00:34:38.450
Come back here in two days
for a wound check.

850
00:34:38.451 --> 00:34:41.662
See you then. Doctor.

851
00:34:41.663 --> 00:34:45.417
Checking blood flow
to the ovary.

852
00:34:49.588 --> 00:34:52.464
- Something wrong?
- Intermittent torsion.

853
00:34:52.465 --> 00:34:54.133
What's that?

854
00:34:54.134 --> 00:34:56.635
I'm coming out now.

855
00:34:56.636 --> 00:34:58.804
We will slide you back. Thanks.

856
00:34:58.805 --> 00:35:02.433
Your ovary is twisting

857
00:35:02.434 --> 00:35:04.143
and cutting off
the blood supply.

858
00:35:04.144 --> 00:35:06.145
That's what's been causing
your pain.

859
00:35:06.146 --> 00:35:09.690
Ah. You said the blood supply
was fine before.

860
00:35:09.691 --> 00:35:13.277
Sometimes the ovary
can twist randomly.

861
00:35:13.278 --> 00:35:16.822
In those cases.
the pain can come and go.

862
00:35:16.823 --> 00:35:19.950
- Can you fix it?
- With surgery.

863
00:35:19.951 --> 00:35:21.201
"Surgery"?

864
00:35:21.202 --> 00:35:23.037
The ovary needs to be untwisted

865
00:35:23.038 --> 00:35:26.040
and tacked down with a stitch
so this doesn't happen again.

866
00:35:26.041 --> 00:35:29.501
If we can get you upstairs
quickly. we can save it.

867
00:35:29.502 --> 00:35:32.004
I could lose my ovary?

868
00:35:32.005 --> 00:35:33.922
Will I still be able
to have a baby?

869
00:35:33.923 --> 00:35:36.175
This shouldn't be
an issue in the future.

870
00:35:36.176 --> 00:35:37.843
Dr. McKay made the right call

871
00:35:37.844 --> 00:35:39.928
to keep you in the ER
for observation

872
00:35:39.929 --> 00:35:43.724
so we could catch it
if the pain returned.

873
00:35:43.725 --> 00:35:45.225
Thank you.

874
00:35:45.226 --> 00:35:48.103
{\an8}- I'll call GYN.
- Yeah.

875
00:35:49.856 --> 00:35:51.857
- Hey. welcome back.
- How was the trip?

876
00:35:51.858 --> 00:35:53.901
- Smooth sailing.
- Presby's pretty nice.

877
00:35:53.902 --> 00:35:56.612
I might have to pick up
some day shifts over there.

878
00:35:56.613 --> 00:35:58.697
<i>Dr. Abbot's funny.</i>

879
00:35:58.698 --> 00:36:00.658
Trust me. his charm wears off.

880
00:36:00.659 --> 00:36:02.242
- No. it doesn't.
- He's not sedated?

881
00:36:02.243 --> 00:36:04.536
I gave him Versed for
the CT scan on the ride back.

882
00:36:04.537 --> 00:36:06.538
but I figured he'd need to be
awake and alert

883
00:36:06.539 --> 00:36:07.831
- to give consent.
- "Consent"?

884
00:36:07.832 --> 00:36:09.416
- Yep.
- We're going to get you settled.

885
00:36:09.417 --> 00:36:11.502
Why don't you page Garcia
to come down?

886
00:36:11.503 --> 00:36:13.253
- Dr. Robby.
- You got this?

887
00:36:13.254 --> 00:36:15.422
- You know I got it.
- Yep.

888
00:36:15.423 --> 00:36:17.508
All right. Howard.

889
00:36:17.509 --> 00:36:19.677
Hey. I want to debrief
with you later

890
00:36:19.678 --> 00:36:21.095
on your sigmoid volvulus
patient.

891
00:36:21.096 --> 00:36:22.888
I finished with your
fireworks kid's sister.

892
00:36:22.889 --> 00:36:24.264
- And?
- She's a responsible

893
00:36:24.265 --> 00:36:25.933
young woman
and a good guardian to Jude.

894
00:36:25.934 --> 00:36:28.185
There is no reason to get
family services involved today.

895
00:36:28.186 --> 00:36:29.561
That's good.

896
00:36:29.562 --> 00:36:31.230
Because he's
in the hospital for surgery.

897
00:36:31.231 --> 00:36:33.232
but they will most likely make
a home visit next week

898
00:36:33.233 --> 00:36:34.900
to evaluate the safety
of their apartment

899
00:36:34.901 --> 00:36:36.443
and the care
that Chantal can provide.

900
00:36:36.444 --> 00:36:38.070
along with her
other responsibilities.

901
00:36:38.071 --> 00:36:39.780
And then what? They take Jude?

902
00:36:39.781 --> 00:36:42.074
In my experience. they'll
make the same assessment I did.

903
00:36:42.075 --> 00:36:43.784
They don't like
to separate siblings.

904
00:36:43.785 --> 00:36:45.577
Anything else we can do for 'em?

905
00:36:45.578 --> 00:36:47.496
I'll get some resources
together for Chantal...

906
00:36:47.497 --> 00:36:49.081
summer after-school programs.

907
00:36:49.082 --> 00:36:51.083
But there might come a point
when he'd be better off

908
00:36:51.084 --> 00:36:52.334
with his parents in Haiti.

909
00:36:52.335 --> 00:36:53.794
His parents want him
to stay here.

910
00:36:53.795 --> 00:36:55.295
It's what's best for the child.

911
00:36:55.296 --> 00:36:56.922
- Says who?
- Dr. Santos.

912
00:36:56.923 --> 00:36:58.174
Come on.

913
00:36:59.968 --> 00:37:02.219
- Welcome back. Mr. Knox.
- What did we discover?

914
00:37:02.220 --> 00:37:04.930
Diverticular abscess
that progressed to perforation.

915
00:37:04.931 --> 00:37:06.765
now with free air
under the diaphragm.

916
00:37:06.766 --> 00:37:08.600
<i>In English. please?</i>

917
00:37:08.601 --> 00:37:10.269
There's a small hole
in the colon

918
00:37:10.270 --> 00:37:11.979
that's spilling bacteria
into the abdomen.

919
00:37:11.980 --> 00:37:15.941
You're likely to develop
peritonitis and sepsis.

920
00:37:15.942 --> 00:37:17.609
<i>How bad?</i>

921
00:37:17.610 --> 00:37:19.069
You need surgery now.

922
00:37:19.070 --> 00:37:22.781
You have a 100% chance
of death without it.

923
00:37:22.782 --> 00:37:24.367
<i>With it?</i>

924
00:37:26.578 --> 00:37:28.621
50% chance.

925
00:37:31.249 --> 00:37:32.791
<i>I could die?</i>

926
00:37:32.792 --> 00:37:34.918
Yes. but we're very good
at what we do.

927
00:37:34.919 --> 00:37:37.880
That is what the consent is for.

928
00:37:37.881 --> 00:37:39.798
<i>What about my sister?</i>

929
00:37:39.799 --> 00:37:42.342
- We found her.
- She'd like to speak with you.

930
00:37:42.343 --> 00:37:44.011
We don't have time for that.

931
00:37:44.012 --> 00:37:46.513
Any delay increases
your mortality risks.

932
00:37:46.514 --> 00:37:49.601
<i>I want
to talk to my sister first.</i>

933
00:37:52.896 --> 00:37:55.731
We're gonna make
that happen for you.

934
00:37:55.732 --> 00:37:59.067
I'll have them prep an OR.
but make it fast. very fast.

935
00:37:59.068 --> 00:38:02.237
Yeah. We're on the move
again. Howard.

936
00:38:16.669 --> 00:38:18.421
Hey.

937
00:38:20.340 --> 00:38:22.717
The ice cream party over?

938
00:38:24.511 --> 00:38:26.678
Yes.

939
00:38:26.679 --> 00:38:29.890
Do you need anything?

940
00:38:31.684 --> 00:38:33.728
A time machine.

941
00:38:37.607 --> 00:38:39.859
That'd be nice. wouldn't it?

942
00:38:44.197 --> 00:38:47.366
I don't even know
what hurts more...

943
00:38:47.367 --> 00:38:50.453
the cancer or...

944
00:38:52.580 --> 00:38:56.084
Knowing I'm never gonna see
my sons grow up.

945
00:38:58.461 --> 00:39:00.880
It feels like a cruel joke.

946
00:39:02.382 --> 00:39:07.052
Why give me children
and a husband I adore

947
00:39:07.053 --> 00:39:10.889
if you're just gonna
take them away from me?

948
00:39:10.890 --> 00:39:14.351
For what? Fucking lung cancer.

949
00:39:17.522 --> 00:39:19.523
I didn't even smoke.

950
00:39:27.448 --> 00:39:29.576
Do you believe in God?

951
00:39:31.870 --> 00:39:34.080
I like the concept.

952
00:39:37.959 --> 00:39:41.336
I'm sure you've seen
a lot of death.

953
00:39:41.337 --> 00:39:43.339
I have seen my share.

954
00:39:46.092 --> 00:39:48.136
Any advice?

955
00:39:53.766 --> 00:39:56.519
I've never died before.

956
00:40:05.820 --> 00:40:07.613
Hey. sorry. W-we're outside.

957
00:40:07.614 --> 00:40:11.158
There's. um... there's no
cell service inside right now.

958
00:40:11.159 --> 00:40:12.660
but. um. here he is.

959
00:40:14.913 --> 00:40:16.413
<i>Oh. my God.</i>

960
00:40:16.414 --> 00:40:18.708
<i>Are you all right?</i>

961
00:40:19.959 --> 00:40:21.752
<i>Been better.</i>

962
00:40:21.753 --> 00:40:24.129
<i>You look beautiful.</i>

963
00:40:24.130 --> 00:40:25.756
<i>Thank you.</i>

964
00:40:25.757 --> 00:40:27.967
<i>You're not looking so hot.</i>

965
00:40:30.094 --> 00:40:32.889
<i>Thank you for calling back.</i>

966
00:40:35.099 --> 00:40:36.808
<i>Of course.</i>

967
00:40:36.809 --> 00:40:39.728
<i>I'm sorry
that it's been this long.</i>

968
00:40:39.729 --> 00:40:43.315
<i>All the stuff with Dad
and the drinking. I...</i>

969
00:40:43.316 --> 00:40:46.485
<i>I had to do what was best
for me and Tommy.</i>

970
00:40:46.486 --> 00:40:48.987
<i>How is Tommy?</i>

971
00:40:48.988 --> 00:40:52.991
<i>Starting his junior year
in high school next month.</i>

972
00:40:52.992 --> 00:40:56.371
<i>16 and already has a girlfriend.</i>

973
00:40:58.331 --> 00:41:00.666
<i>Takes after his uncle.</i>

974
00:41:02.710 --> 00:41:04.378
<i>Maybe we can make a plan</i>

975
00:41:04.379 --> 00:41:07.090
<i>for you to see each other
over the holidays.</i>

976
00:41:11.302 --> 00:41:13.388
<i>I'd love that.</i>

977
00:41:14.847 --> 00:41:16.683
<i>Is the doctor there?</i>

978
00:41:18.476 --> 00:41:20.018
Hi. I'm Dr. Abbot.

979
00:41:20.019 --> 00:41:21.812
<i>Can you call me
when he gets out of surgery?</i>

980
00:41:21.813 --> 00:41:23.981
Of course. but right now we
need to get him up to the OR.

981
00:41:23.982 --> 00:41:25.565
<i>I understand. Thanks.</i>

982
00:41:25.566 --> 00:41:27.360
<i>Talk to you soon. Howard.</i>

983
00:41:29.362 --> 00:41:32.906
<i>Oh. I forgot to tell him
I love him.</i>

984
00:41:32.907 --> 00:41:34.199
Oh. wow.

985
00:41:34.200 --> 00:41:36.076
Monica?

986
00:41:36.077 --> 00:41:37.369
Welcome back.

987
00:41:37.370 --> 00:41:39.413
Robinavitch.

988
00:41:39.414 --> 00:41:42.207
- Two for the lab. three for CT.
- I'll take those.

989
00:41:42.208 --> 00:41:44.918
- They need me upstairs.
- On it for CT.

990
00:41:44.919 --> 00:41:46.211
You run a tight ship.

991
00:41:46.212 --> 00:41:48.255
Well. it's a work in progress.

992
00:41:48.256 --> 00:41:50.716
- Is he going up?
- Yeah.

993
00:41:50.717 --> 00:41:53.385
He's a good guy.

994
00:41:53.386 --> 00:41:56.221
Our surgeons
will get him through.

995
00:42:00.143 --> 00:42:02.894
I like her.

996
00:42:02.895 --> 00:42:04.646
More than me?

997
00:42:04.647 --> 00:42:07.107
Only time will tell.

998
00:42:07.108 --> 00:42:08.984
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

999
00:42:08.985 --> 00:42:11.611
She has good command
of staff and procedures.

1000
00:42:11.612 --> 00:42:14.906
I think you're leaving your day
shift in very capable hands.

1001
00:42:14.907 --> 00:42:16.408
I hope so.

1002
00:42:16.409 --> 00:42:18.368
All right. I'm out of here. man.

1003
00:42:18.369 --> 00:42:21.455
I got to be back
in a few hours for my shift.

1004
00:42:21.456 --> 00:42:23.290
Well. hey. if I don't see you...

1005
00:42:23.291 --> 00:42:26.043
You're really doing this still?

1006
00:42:26.044 --> 00:42:28.086
I don't think I can remember
the last time

1007
00:42:28.087 --> 00:42:29.629
you took three days off
in a row.

1008
00:42:29.630 --> 00:42:32.424
I've taken a vacation before.

1009
00:42:32.425 --> 00:42:34.384
Name the last one.

1010
00:42:36.971 --> 00:42:39.389
Point taken.

1011
00:42:39.390 --> 00:42:42.685
It's gonna be a lot of time
to self-reflect.

1012
00:42:45.104 --> 00:42:47.315
You sure you can handle that?

1013
00:42:49.609 --> 00:42:51.443
Okay.

1014
00:42:51.444 --> 00:42:53.612
You just make sure
you come back.

1015
00:42:53.613 --> 00:42:56.324
And if it gets dark.
you call me.

1016
00:42:57.950 --> 00:42:59.702
You listening?

1017
00:43:04.165 --> 00:43:06.458
So the ankle's negative
for fracture.

1018
00:43:06.459 --> 00:43:08.627
Wait. go back to the ankle.

1019
00:43:08.628 --> 00:43:10.170
You see the normal mortise?

1020
00:43:10.171 --> 00:43:13.298
Yeah. but the tibiofibular
clear space looks enlarged.

1021
00:43:13.299 --> 00:43:16.468
and the tibiofibular overlap
seems reduced.

1022
00:43:16.469 --> 00:43:19.846
Maybe a little.

1023
00:43:19.847 --> 00:43:22.933
8 millimeters. 3 millimeters.

1024
00:43:22.934 --> 00:43:25.352
Seems like a tear
in the syndesmotic ligaments.

1025
00:43:25.353 --> 00:43:27.479
Doesn't that need
surgical fixation?

1026
00:43:27.480 --> 00:43:30.440
They do. I can request an MRI.

1027
00:43:30.441 --> 00:43:33.652
Um. have you done
a radiology clerkship before?

1028
00:43:33.653 --> 00:43:36.572
No. I'm just that good.

1029
00:43:38.324 --> 00:43:42.035
I'm good at things. too.

1030
00:43:52.046 --> 00:43:57.050
Really great work
earlier today. Doctor.

1031
00:43:57.051 --> 00:43:59.719
Huh.

1032
00:43:59.720 --> 00:44:01.054
Ow. wow.

1033
00:44:01.055 --> 00:44:03.515
- You can just call me Whitaker.
- Not a chance.

1034
00:44:03.516 --> 00:44:04.766
You earned that.

1035
00:44:04.767 --> 00:44:06.184
I'm proud of you.

1036
00:44:06.185 --> 00:44:07.894
We all are.

1037
00:44:07.895 --> 00:44:09.146
Thank you.

1038
00:44:09.147 --> 00:44:11.606
- Busy day.
- Oh. yeah.

1039
00:44:11.607 --> 00:44:14.401
So you're
a very empathetic soul.

1040
00:44:14.402 --> 00:44:16.695
- Yeah. I'd like to think...
- I'm not finished yet.

1041
00:44:16.696 --> 00:44:19.072
And you want to be there
for all your patients.

1042
00:44:19.073 --> 00:44:20.740
- Don't you?
- Shh.

1043
00:44:20.741 --> 00:44:22.033
Sorry.

1044
00:44:22.034 --> 00:44:24.327
So this relationship
that you're having

1045
00:44:24.328 --> 00:44:26.830
with this woman. um.
the widow of the burn victim

1046
00:44:26.831 --> 00:44:28.665
- who died last year.
- Amy.

1047
00:44:28.666 --> 00:44:30.041
Santos tell you?

1048
00:44:30.042 --> 00:44:32.502
I understand
you're helping her out.

1049
00:44:32.503 --> 00:44:34.337
Yeah. on the farm.

1050
00:44:34.338 --> 00:44:37.215
I grew up on one. and Amy's...

1051
00:44:37.216 --> 00:44:39.843
Mrs. Miller is getting
pressure to sell.

1052
00:44:39.844 --> 00:44:42.012
so I'm just helping out.

1053
00:44:42.013 --> 00:44:44.055
What about her friends
and family?

1054
00:44:44.056 --> 00:44:45.891
Yeah. they're around.

1055
00:44:45.892 --> 00:44:47.392
Supporting her?

1056
00:44:47.393 --> 00:44:48.977
Yeah. I think they try to.

1057
00:44:48.978 --> 00:44:52.397
but. mostly.
she's just leaning on...

1058
00:44:52.398 --> 00:44:53.816
me.

1059
00:44:56.736 --> 00:44:58.737
I'm sure she's really grateful

1060
00:44:58.738 --> 00:45:00.155
for everything that you do.

1061
00:45:00.156 --> 00:45:03.116
but it's important
to have boundaries.

1062
00:45:03.117 --> 00:45:04.452
Yeah.

1063
00:45:07.622 --> 00:45:10.749
Hey. you want to do me a favor?

1064
00:45:10.750 --> 00:45:12.083
Yeah?

1065
00:45:12.084 --> 00:45:14.920
You want to house-sit for me
while I'm gone?

1066
00:45:14.921 --> 00:45:16.922
You'd actually be
helping me out.

1067
00:45:16.923 --> 00:45:20.258
and you could save
some money on rent.

1068
00:45:20.259 --> 00:45:21.760
Are you being serious?

1069
00:45:21.761 --> 00:45:24.804
No smoking. no parties.
no pets. no babies.

1070
00:45:24.805 --> 00:45:26.598
yours or anybody else's.

1071
00:45:26.599 --> 00:45:29.267
- I don't have a baby.
- No. but she does.

1072
00:45:29.268 --> 00:45:32.395
I was going to ask Abbot. but
he does nude yoga at sunrise.

1073
00:45:32.396 --> 00:45:34.606
and I don't think some
of my elderly neighbors

1074
00:45:34.607 --> 00:45:36.900
would survive seeing that.

1075
00:45:36.901 --> 00:45:39.945
Yeah.
Yeah. t-that would be amazing...

1076
00:45:39.946 --> 00:45:43.406
the house-sitting.
not seeing Abbot's naked yoga.

1077
00:45:43.407 --> 00:45:46.117
If I don't come back. you got
a swinging bachelor pad.

1078
00:45:46.118 --> 00:45:47.536
Okay.

1079
00:45:48.913 --> 00:45:50.580
Come find me before you leave.

1080
00:45:50.581 --> 00:45:52.916
I'll give you my keys
and the security code.

1081
00:45:52.917 --> 00:45:54.167
Okay.

1082
00:45:54.168 --> 00:45:57.462
Who's the joker that did this?

1083
00:45:57.463 --> 00:45:59.547
Oh.

1084
00:45:59.548 --> 00:46:01.132
We need some help out there.

1085
00:46:01.133 --> 00:46:03.301
You two. make sure
to double-check your work.

1086
00:46:03.302 --> 00:46:04.886
Triage could use an extra hand.

1087
00:46:04.887 --> 00:46:06.972
Princess. finish up here.
then head that way.

1088
00:46:06.973 --> 00:46:09.307
- Three for CT now.
- Should I run it over?

1089
00:46:09.308 --> 00:46:10.976
No. Keep taking off orders.

1090
00:46:10.977 --> 00:46:13.061
CT's gonna get backed up
if we wait on these.

1091
00:46:13.062 --> 00:46:15.188
I know. but I can't waste
a runner on that right now.

1092
00:46:15.189 --> 00:46:17.232
Where'd you find
a carrier sheet?

1093
00:46:17.233 --> 00:46:20.068
Exactly where I filed it away
ten years ago.

1094
00:46:20.069 --> 00:46:22.153
I thought that thing
didn't work.

1095
00:46:22.154 --> 00:46:24.030
Can't receive. but it can send.

1096
00:46:31.122 --> 00:46:34.457
Stay hydrated. preferably
with electrolyte-rich drinks

1097
00:46:34.458 --> 00:46:36.710
- like coconut water.
- I'm not a fan of coconuts.

1098
00:46:36.711 --> 00:46:38.336
Okay. Gatorade's also an option.

1099
00:46:38.337 --> 00:46:40.672
Just avoid alcohol and
caffeine. and I suggest wearing

1100
00:46:40.673 --> 00:46:42.340
- light. breathable clothing.
- Boring.

1101
00:46:42.341 --> 00:46:44.301
Come back
if your symptoms worsen.

1102
00:46:44.302 --> 00:46:46.052
if you develop
a headache or confusion.

1103
00:46:46.053 --> 00:46:47.345
Okay.

1104
00:46:47.346 --> 00:46:50.348
Mm. You sure about that?

1105
00:46:52.351 --> 00:46:55.395
Hey. could you turn that up?

1106
00:46:55.396 --> 00:46:58.732
<i>Have responded to a deadly
waterslide collapse</i>

1107
00:46:58.733 --> 00:47:00.233
<i>at a local water park.</i>

1108
00:47:00.234 --> 00:47:02.402
<i>Now. we're told there's
at least one fatality.</i>

1109
00:47:02.403 --> 00:47:03.737
<i>with multiple injuries.</i>

1110
00:47:03.738 --> 00:47:06.865
- Oh. shit.
- And they're all coming to us.

1111
00:47:06.866 --> 00:47:09.785
<i>Currently being airlifted
to the hospital by heli...</i>

